    <button type="submit" id="promo-button">Submit</button>
  </form>

  <div id="hires" class="hide">
    <p id="hires-info">
      Thank you for supporting The Moment. These files are the high resolution digital masters that
      were pressed into the vinyl records. They are 24bit 96k files. CDs are only 16bit 44.1k files
      for comparison. CDs can also be mastered louder than vinyl which means that there is more
      compression of each track to get them to seem louder. Vinyl needs to have a lower level to
      avoid distortion, so a lot of the final compression is removed. This results in a file that is
      more true to the original mix and has more dynmaics than a CD master. I hope you enjoy them.
    </p>
